\C[6]When they joined the rest of the disciples,
they saw a large crowd around them and some
teachers of the Law arguing with them.
\C[6]When the people saw Jesus, they were greatly
surprised, and ran to him and greeted him.
What are you arguing with them about?
Teacher, I brought my son to you, because he
has an evil spirit in him and cannot talk.
Whenever the spirit attacks him, it throws him
to the ground, and he foams at the mouth...
...grits his teeth, and becomes stiff all over.
I asked your disciples to drive the spirit out,
How unbelieving you people are! How long must I
stay with you? How long do I have to put up
with you? Bring the boy to me!
\C[6]They brought him to Jesus. As soon as the
spirit saw Jesus, it threw the boy into a fit,
so that he fell on the ground and rolled around
How long has he been like this?
Ever since he was a child. Many times the evil
spirit has tried to kill him by throwing him in
the fire and into water. Have pity on us and
help us, if you possibly can!
Yes, if you yourself can! Everything is
possible for the person who has faith.
I do have faith, but not enough.

Deaf and dumb spirit, I order you to come out

fit, and came out. The boy looked like a corpse
\C[6]But Jesus took the boy by the hand and
helped him rise, and he stood up.

Desde niño; y muchas veces le echa en el fuego

¡Para el que cree, todo es posible!
Creo, Señor, ayuda a mi incredulidad.

\C[6]Quan van arribar on eren els altres deixebles,
veieren una gentada al seu voltant i uns
mestres de la Llei que discutien amb ells.
\C[6]Tota la gent, sorpresos de veure Jesús, anaren
corrents a saludar-lo. Jesús els preguntà:
Mestre, t'he portat el meu fill, posseït d'un
esperit que el priva de parlar. Quan se
n'apodera, sigui on sigui, el tira per terra,
i el noi treu bromera, cruix de dents i...
...es queda rígid. He dit als teus deixebles
que l'hi traguessin, però no han pogut.
Generació descreguda! Fins quan hauré d'estar
amb vosaltres? Fins quan us hauré de suportar?
\C[6]Ells l'hi portaren. Així que el noi veié
Jesús, l'esperit el sacsejà violentament; el
noi caigué a terra i es rebolcava traient
Des de quan li passa això?
Des de petit. Sovint l'ha tirat al foc i a
l'aigua per matar-lo. Si hi pots fer res,
Em dius si puc fer-hi res...
Tot és possible al qui creu.
Crec, però ajuda'm a tenir més fe.
\C[6]Jesús, veient que hi acudia més gent, increpà

surt d'aquest noi i no hi tornis més.
\C[6]Llavors l'esperit va sortir enmig de xiscles
i de grans convulsions, i el noi quedà com
mort: tothom deia que ja no vivia.
\C[6]Però Jesús el va prendre per la mà,
el va aixecar i el noi es posà dret.
Now you can leave the mountain.
Ahora ya puedes irte del monte.
Ara ja et pots anar-te'n de la muntanya.
